longBusinessSummary: Givaudan SA, together with its subsidiaries, manufactures, supplies, and sells fragrance, beauty, flavor, and wellbeing products to the consumer goods industries. The company operates through two divisions, Fragrance & Beauty and Taste & Wellbeing. The Fragrance & Beauty division provides fine fragrances, consumer products, and fragrance ingredients and active beauty products. The Taste & Wellbeing division offers beverages, such as soft drinks, fruit juices, instant beverages, etc.; dairy products, including dairy drinks, yoghurt, ice cream, chilled desserts, cream cheese, and spreads; savory products comprising ready-made meals, noodles, processed meat and snacks, and poultry products; snacks consisting of rice crackers, cassava chips, and potato crisps; and biscuits and crackers, cereals, confectionery, chewing gums, chocolates, and candies. It operates in Switzerland, Europe, Africa, the Middle East, North America, Latin America, and the Asia Pacific. The company was founded in 1796 and is headquartered in Vernier, Switzerland.
